Etymology:— The specific epithet honors Friedrich Sello(w) (1789–1831), a German naturalist who carried out expeditions in Brazil between 1814 and 1831 ( Vasconcelos & Pacheco 2012 ). The spelling of this specific epithet is “
sellovii
” and not “ sellowii ”, because Schultz-Bipontinus made an implicit Latinization of the surname when describing the species (ICN, Art. 60.9;
Turland et al. 2018
), thus this spelling should be preserved over “sellowii”.
